What is the meaning of a leased line egypt connection?

LeasedLine

refers to a dedicated communication channel that easily interconnects two or more sites. Actually, it is a service contract between a provider and a customer. This dedicated line ensures continuous data flow from one point to another for a fixed monthly rate. Leased line usage is popular in data, internet, and telephone services. LeasedLine connection depends on fiber optic cable in order to provide high-quality bandwidth and speed.

Generally, it used for-

  • Carry phone calls
  • Link servers and PCs in different offices
  • To connect to the internet with very high speed
  • Make it possible for staffs to their work PCs from home

What is a fiber leasedline? What are its advantages?

A leased-line is also known as a fiber leased line egypt

The LeasedLine is a dedicated fiber-optic service and connects directly to the premises. LeasedLine can directly connect to the public internet through a dedicated fiber optic cable. Here you do not need to share the infrastructure. Fiber SDSL is there solely for the purpose of serving you and it is not shared with any other individual or user. The speed of this leased line ranges from 1 Mbps Speed to 10 Gbps Speed.
